# Astro 5 Patterns

## Content Collections

- Use Content Collections with Zod schemas for all content (blog, etc.).
- Define schemas in `content.config.ts` with `defineCollection` and `z.object()`.

```typescript
// content.config.ts
import { defineCollection, z } from 'astro:content';

const blog = defineCollection({
  loader: glob({ base: './src/content/blog', pattern: '**/*.{md,mdx}' }),
  schema: z.object({
    title: z.string(),
    description: z.string(),
    publishedAt: z.coerce.date(),
    tags: z.array(z.string()).default([]),
    draft: z.boolean().default(false),
  }),
});
```

## Component Choice

- **Prefer Astro components** for static content (layouts, blog cards, landing sections).
- Use React/Vue/Svelte only when interactivity is needed (chat widgets, forms, client-side state).

```astro
---
// ✅ Good - Astro for static content
---

<article class="post-card">
  <h2>{post.title}</h2>
  <p>{post.excerpt}</p>
</article>
```

## Client Directives

- `client:load` only when needed immediately (e.g. chat widget).
- Prefer `client:visible` for below-the-fold content (lazy hydration).
- Use `client:idle` for non-critical interactivity.

```astro
<!-- ✅ Good - Visible when in viewport -->
<ChatWidget client:visible />

<!-- ❌ Avoid - Loads immediately -->
<ChatWidget client:load />

<!-- ✅ Good - When above fold and critical -->
<Header client:load />
```

## View Transitions

- Enable View Transitions for page navigation where appropriate.
- Use `<ViewTransitions />` in layout or `<Transition />` for partial updates.

```astro
---
import { ViewTransitions } from 'astro:transitions';
---

<head>
  <ViewTransitions />
</head>
```

## Path Aliases

Use project aliases for imports:

| Alias | Path |
|-------|------|
| `@components/` | `./src/components/*` |
| `@layouts/` | `./src/layouts/*` |
| `@lib/` | `./src/lib/*` |
| `@/` | `./src/*` |

```astro
---
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PostCard from '@components/blog/PostCard.astro';
import { getPostBySlug } from '@lib/content';
---
```

## Image Optimization

- Use `astro:assets` for optimized images.
- Prefer `<Image>` component for responsive images.

```astro
---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
---

<Image src={post.coverImage} alt={post.title} width={800} />
```

## Class Binding

- Use `class:list` for conditional classes in Astro.

```astro
<article class:list={['post-card', { 'post-card--featured': post.featured }]}>
```
